parent_allowance: Building services staff; maintenance staff (inclusive only of carpenters, joiners and painters); and trades staff (excluding plumbers)
allowance: Hot work (54°C and over) + - In places where the temperature exceeds 54°C; - Where the work continues for 2 or more hours in temperatures exceeding 54°C employees will be entitled to a rest period of 20 minutes every 2 hours (without loss of pay)

parent_allowance: Building services staff; maintenance staff (inclusive only of carpenters, joiners and painters); and trades staff (excluding plumbers)
allowance: Insulation materials + Where employees are handling charcoal, pumice, granulated cork, silicate of cotton, insulwool, slag wool, or other recognized insulating material of a like nature, associated with similar disabilities in its use
Leading hand—11–20 employees + Where the leading hand is in charge of 11–20 employees
Leading hand—3–10 employees + Where the leading hand is in charge of 3–10 employees
Leading hand—more than 20 employees + Where the leading hand is in charge of more than 20 employees

parent_allowance: Maintenance staff (inclusive only of builders labourers)
allowance: Lifting—5.5–9kg blocks + - Where required to lift blocks (other than cindrete blocks for plugging purposes)

allowance: Lifting—more than 18kg blocks + - Where required to lift blocks (other than cindrete blocks for plugging purposes); - Employees will not be required to lift blocks in excess of 20kg unless they are provided with a mechanical aid or with an assisting employee

Relieving officer + Where appointed as a relieving officer (relieves at short notice another security officer, a display roster is not required and 24 hours' notice of shift will be given where possible)

parent_allowance: Maintenance staff (inclusive only of carpenters or joiners)
allowance: Roofing repairs + Where engaged in repairs to roofs

parent_allowance: Maintenance staff (inclusive only of carpenters or joiners)
allowance: Second-hand timber + Where working with second-hand timber and the employee's tools are damaged by nail, dumps or other foreign matter on the timber; - Damage must be immediately reported to their supervisor

Sleepover allowance + - Where an employee (permanently residing on campus) is required to sleep-over at the employer's premises for a period outside the employee's ordinary hours of duty; - sleep-over period will not commence prior to 10.00 pm; - In addition to this allowance, an employee will be paid as follows: - for work less than one hour—nil - for work more than one hour—in accordance with overtime provisions

parent_allowance: Maintenance staff (inclusive only of carpenters, joiners and painters)
allowance: Toxic substances + - Employees engaged in preparation and/or application of epoxy based materials, materials of a like nature or toxic materials; - Employees in close proximity to other employees so engaged

allowance: Wet work + Where employees are working in any place where their clothing becomes saturated by water, oil or another substance they must be paid the allowance for every hour so engaged unless supplied with protective clothing and/or footwear
